	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64190990">Why not add a digital signature to the true GPS signal?  Since the signal includes time as well as position information, timestamps are automatically built in to prevent replay attacks.  (The receiver would need to first fix on a true signal to set its internal clock, but this could be done before entering hostile territory.)  The USSF (the organization that runs the GPS system) could publish public keys which could then be incorporated in receivers. Signals could still be jammed, but they could not be spoo</div>
	</div>

